      "description": "Investigates long-running local runtime failures with logs, processes, exclusive resources, and a tight reproduction loop.",
      "displayName": "Dev Runtime Diagnostician",
      "dynamicFolderSkills": true,
      "examples": [
        {
          "plausibleResponse": "Reproduced the failure with a start-stop-start sequence and correlated the bind error with the process tree and shutdown logs. A child process survives the normal stop path and retains the configured port. Identified the lifecycle boundary, proposed waiting for child termination before restart, and verified that terminating the retained process restores three consecutive clean restarts.",
          "purpose": "Diagnose a repeatable local service startup failure by identifying the process lifecycle and exclusive resource that prevent a clean restart.",
          "runtimeInvocations": {
            "claude-code": "@agent-dev-runtime-diagnostician Investigate why the local service cannot bind its configured port after a normal restart, and identify the narrowest verified resolution path.",
            "codex": "$dev-runtime-diagnostician Investigate why the local service cannot bind its configured port after a normal restart, and identify the narrowest verified resolution path."
          }
        },
        {
          "plausibleResponse": "Reproduced the stall with a bounded workload and traced task handling through the connection-leasing boundary. Logs and pool metrics ruled out queue starvation and CPU saturation, then showed cancelled tasks retaining every available connection. Identified the cancellation cleanup path as the suspected boundary, specified a focused release-on-cancel regression test, and reported the sustained verification run required to confirm the remediation.",
          "purpose": "Isolate a long-running worker stall by combining a focused reproduction, execution tracing, and runtime evidence to distinguish competing failure hypotheses.",
          "runtimeInvocations": {
            "claude-code": "@agent-dev-runtime-diagnostician Diagnose why the local background worker stops making progress during a sustained test while the process remains alive.",
            "codex": "$dev-runtime-diagnostician Diagnose why the local background worker stops making progress during a sustained test while the process remains alive."
          }
        }
      ],
      "filename": "dev-runtime-diagnostician",
      "group": "dev-activities",
      "groupLabel": "Dev Activities",
      "instructionSections": {},
      "instructions": "Reproduce the failure with the technology guidance supplied for the active scope, isolate the runtime boundary, gather logs and process evidence, and propose the narrowest verified fix path.",
      "modelProfile": "advanced",
